# Project Invariants (Always On)

This repository is benchmark-first, agent-second.

## Scope Lock (v1)
- Only three task families are in v1:
  1. severe hyperkalemia response
  2. severe hypoglycemia response
  3. sustained hypotension response
- Reject work that broadens v1 into a generic ICU copilot.

## Non-Negotiable Contract
- No future leakage.
- Labels must be deterministic and reproducible.
- Splits must be reproducible and leakage-safe.
- Keep protocol-derived gold action labels separate from observed clinician actions.
- Agent/tool interfaces must be structured and timestamp-bounded.
- Outputs must be strict, machine-scorable JSON (no vague free text).
- Claims must stay benchmark-focused and avoid physician-equivalence or deployment claims.

## File-creation discipline
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones.
- Every new file must be justified: it exists only when the module is large enough (>~150 lines of logic) or serves a clearly distinct responsibility that would clutter its neighbor.
- Small helpers (<~100 lines), single-function utilities, and thin wrappers should be merged into the closest related module instead of getting their own file.
- Before creating a new package directory, confirm the contents will span at least 2 non-trivial modules beyond `__init__.py`.

## Enforcement
- If a requested change violates these invariants, narrow or rewrite the change so the invariants hold.
- Prefer reproducible benchmark fidelity over feature expansion.
